{"updated_at": {"date": {"d": "27", "m": "04", "Y": "2026"}, "time": {"H": "08", "M": "02", "S": "10"}}, "news": [{"title": "L&T Realty acquires 20 acres land in Gurugram", "para": "L&T Realty Properties has acquired International Green Scapes in Delhi. This move gives LTRPL 20 acres of land in Gurugram. The site has development potential for 3.6 million sq ft. LTRPL and L&T Realty Developers have also completed land acquisitions in Mumbai, Delhi, and Bengaluru. These acquisitions offer a combined development potential of three million sq ft.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/industry/lt-realty-acquires-20-acres-land-in-gurugram/130547106?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-195268/130547106.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "industry"}, {"title": "Villagers oppose commercial, multi-dwelling units at Loliem", "para": "Loliem-Polem villagers unanimously opposed large construction projects, including 36 villas, citing concerns over development. The gram sabha urged the panchayat to prevent mega projects and ensure timely desilting of rivulets and drainage cleaning before the monsoons. A proposal for a dog shelter was deemed unfeasible due to resource limitations.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/commercial/loliem-villagers-unite-against-proposed-multi-dwelling-units/130547848?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-91096/130547848.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "commercial"}, {"title": "Delhi: MCD activates Swagam portal for house regularisation in unauthorised colonies", "para": "Delhi residents in 1,511 unauthorized colonies can now apply for property regularization via the MCD's Swagam portal. The civic body has empanelled architects to assist applicants, streamlining the process for obtaining regularisation certificates. Approvals are on an 'as-is-where-is' basis, with penal charges for excess construction. Awareness camps are being organized to guide residents.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/technology/mcd-launches-swagam-portal-for-property-regularisation-in-unauthorised-delhi-colonies/130547820?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-75596/130547820.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "technology"}]}